<figureCitation id="135D2A47096A0450FD6778AFFCDEFC00" box="[759,828,977,1003]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37C6549096A0450FF2D7F6DFBD5FB2C" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD936C2096A0450FF2D7F6DFED4FBC6" blockId="4.[189,310,1043,1069]" box="[189,310,1043,1069]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading id="D09181AE096A0450FF2D7F6DFED4FBC6" bold="true" box="[189,310,1043,1069]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B912EAD0096A0450FF2D7F6DFED4FBC6" bold="true" box="[189,310,1043,1069]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD936C2096A0450FF2D7F3CFBD5FB2C" blockId="4.[189,1399,1090,1224]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
A key character of 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D41096A0450FE307F3CFD7DFBB7" authority="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof, 2017" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2017" box="[416,671,1090,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujisanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B912EAD0096A0450FE307F3CFD7DFBB7" box="[416,671,1090,1116]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Aprionus fujisanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22157AB096A0450FD377F3CFCE1FBB7" box="[679,771,1090,1116]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the tegmen whose unusually narrow lateral pillars (↓, 
<figureCitation id="135D2A47096A0450FF767F18FEA6FB6B" box="[230,324,1126,1152]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) form a perfect, inverted 
<collectionCodeEnum id="970D72E0096A0450FDEB7F18FD72FB6B" box="[635,656,1126,1152]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">V</collectionCodeEnum>
basally, then run parallel to each other for quite a distance to end in membranous hooks. This conspicuous outline occurs in combination with small ventroposterior gonocoxal lobes (↓, 
<figureCitation id="135D2A47096A0450FE3B7FD3FDE4FB2C" box="[427,518,1197,1223]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) and gonostyli with a narrow apex (↓, 
<figureCitation id="135D2A47096A0450FC5C7FD3FBCBFB2C" box="[972,1065,1197,1223]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[304,1285,950,1881]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[227,1361,943,1887]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Aprionus fujisanensis sp. nov., holotype, ♂. A. Genitalia, ventral. B. Fourth flagellomere, lateral. C. Ninth tergite, dorsal. D. Posterior portion of wing. Scale lines: A–B = 0.05 mm; C = 0.025 mm; D = 0.50 mm. Arrows indicate diagnostic characters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838633/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
